hymn.latin: Placeholder Latin hymn for Easter Sunday Matins
hymn.english: Placeholder English hymn for Easter Sunday Matins

text.latin: Beatus vir, qui non abiit in consilio impiorum...
text.english: Blessed is the man who walks not in the counsel of the wicked...

text.latin: Placeholder Latin reading for Easter Sunday Matins
text.english: Placeholder English reading for Easter Sunday Matins

prayer.latin: Deus, qui hodiérna die per Unigénitum tuum æternitátis nobis áditum, devícta morte, reserásti: vota nostra, quæ præveniéndo aspíras, étiam adjuvándo proséquere.
prayer.english: O God, who, on this day, through Thine only-begotten Son, hast conquered death, and thrown open to us the gate of everlasting life, give effect by thine aid to our desires, which Thou dost anticipate and inspire
